OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1782427691
OL,3,CCQC admits disability care inspections
OL,4,Cmust improve after ITV News
OL,5,Cinvestigation
OL,7,FDr George Julian is an expert in
OL,8,Flearning disability sector who has
OL,9,Fspent a decade reporting on the deaths
OL,10,Fof learning disabled people in care.
OL,12,FShe says the CQC is not doing enough
OL,13,Fto old providers to account.
OL,15,F"I think people with learning
OL,16,Fdisabilities are treated as second
OL,17,Fclass citizens - the care isn't good
OL,18,Fenough, the regulator isn't good
OL,19,Fenough, often coronial processes
OL,20,Faren't good enough, people's deaths
OL,21,Fdon't even get referred to coroners.
OL,26,@wD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G25/27
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31826
SC,0026
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1782427691
OL,3,CCQC admits disability care inspections
OL,4,Cmust improve after ITV News
OL,5,Cinvestigation
OL,7,F"At every level I think people are
OL,8,Fneglected. The providers have got them
OL,9,F(the CQC) over a barrel, because
OL,10,Fthere's not enough good provision,
OL,11,Fthere's not enough provision, and
OL,12,Ftherefore maybe they don't look too
OL,13,Fclosely."
OL,15,FThe CQC robustly deny that is the
OL,16,Fcase, but it is undeniable that a
OL,17,Fchronic shortage of care placements
OL,18,Fmeans Adam, despite everything, is
OL,19,Fstill in the same care home in
OL,20,FSouthampton run by Voyage.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@IO]
